&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;small&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;items&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;74978&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Superior Rune of the Dragonhunter work equally well.&lt;&#x2F;small&gt;
&lt;small&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;items&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;36053&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Superior Sigil of the Night can be situationally better.&lt;&#x2F;small&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;build&quot;&gt;Build&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;pre data-lang=&quot;chatlink&quot; class=&quot;language-chatlink z-code&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-chatlink&quot; data-lang=&quot;chatlink&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-source z-chatlink&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation z-definition z-string z-begin&quot;&gt;[&amp;amp;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;DQUcPSMbBzkMAQwBMwEvAVgBPgFXAVYBKAAoAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAAACWQA2AAA=&lt;span class=&quot;z-punctuation z-definition z-string z-end&quot;&gt;]&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;code&gt;&lt;&#x2F;pre&gt;
&lt;hr &#x2F;&gt;
&lt;div data-armory-embed=&#x27;skills&#x27; data-armory-ids=&#x27;13027,13046,13064,13062,13082&#x27;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;div&gt;&lt;div data-armory-embed=&#x27;specializations&#x27; data-armory-ids=&#x27;28,35,7&#x27; data-armory-28-traits=&#x27;1245,1704,1269&#x27; data-armory-35-traits=&#x27;1268,1272,1904&#x27; data-armory-7-traits=&#x27;1933,1893,2047&#x27;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;div&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;rotation&quot;&gt;Rotation&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;hr &#x2F;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are 2 main resources you have to manage in this rotation, &lt;strong&gt;Initiative&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt; and &lt;strong&gt;Endurance&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are also 2 crucial buffs to upkeep, &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;items&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;100916&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Relic of the Thief and &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;traits&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;2047&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Bounding Dodger.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your skills cost &lt;strong&gt;Initiative&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt; to cast but have no cooldown, and casting a skill refreshes &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;items&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;100916&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Relic of the Thief uptime. Consider &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;items&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;104241&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Relic of the Eagle on some fights. Since &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;29911&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Weakening Whirl (Staff 2) does the most damage per point of &lt;strong&gt;Initiatve&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;, you want to use it as much as possible over all of your other skills. You may press and hold this skill to reduce the number of button presses (APM).&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Dodging activates &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;traits&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;2047&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Bounding Dodger, but costs &lt;strong&gt;Endurance&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;. It is recommended for less experienced players to save at least 1 bar of &lt;strong&gt;Endurance&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt; at all times instead of using it all up. This will result in a minor DPS loss, but allow you to have a dodge in a bad situation.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;By following the below rotation, you will naturally maintain full uptime on &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;items&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;100916&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Relic of the Thief, as well as high uptime on &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;traits&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;2047&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Bounding Dodger.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Precast&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;13082&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Thieves Guild&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;13027&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Hide in Shadows&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Opener:&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dodge to start the fight&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use all your initiative on &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;29911&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Weakening Whirl (Staff 2)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dodge&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Loop:&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use 2 full auto attack chains&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dodge&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Use all your initiative on &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;29911&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Weakening Whirl (Staff 2)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Repeat&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you run out of stamina and cannot dodge after using 2 full auto attack chains, do 1 more auto attack chain for a total of 3 auto attack chains, then continue with step 2.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can also look at your &lt;strong&gt;Endurance&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;, and as soon as you fill up 1 or 2 bars depending on how safe you are playing, finish your current auto attack chain and start from step 2 in the loop.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Your final attack in the auto attack chain, &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;30434&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Punishing Strikes, is a huge twirl of the staff, and is easier to see if you use a flashier staff skin. It also plays a very different sound from the first 2 attacks, and can be used as a point of reference. Try not to cancel &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;30434&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Punishing Strikes, as a large part of your damage comes from &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;30434&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Punishing Strikes.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;utilties&quot;&gt;Utilties&lt;&#x2F;h4&gt;
&lt;hr &#x2F;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You may replace following skills for extra utilities a small&#x2F;minimal DPS loss:&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;13062&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Signet of Agility -&amp;gt; &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;13057&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Prepare Pitfall (for precasted opener is a DPS gain)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;13064&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Infiltrator&#x27;s Signet&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;13082&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Thieves Guild&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;crowd-control&quot;&gt;Crowd Control&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;hr &#x2F;&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;30210&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Hook Strike (Stealth Attack)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;30520&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Debilitating Arc -&amp;gt; &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;71802&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Helmet Breaker&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;30868&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Fist Flurry -&amp;gt; &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;30693&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Palm Strike&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;13132&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Basilisk Venom (Elite Swap)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;56880&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Pitfall (Utility Swap)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;small&gt;Note: You may use &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;13027&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Hide in Shadows to access the Stealth Attack for CC.&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&quot;advanced-tips&quot;&gt;Advanced Tips&lt;&#x2F;h2&gt;
&lt;hr &#x2F;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can use &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;13014&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Steal whenever it is off cooldown to instantly regain 1 bar of &lt;strong&gt;Endurance&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;. You may switch one of the auto attack chains with &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;30868&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Fist Flurry -&amp;gt; &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;30693&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Palm Strike for a small DPS gain, which can be press and held to cast the skill chain.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is also recommended for advance players to bring an alternative set of weapons:&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;table class=&quot;weapontable&quot;&gt;
&lt;thead&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;th&gt;Weapon&lt;&#x2F;th&gt;&lt;th&gt;Type&lt;&#x2F;th&gt;&lt;th&gt;Stat&lt;&#x2F;th&gt;&lt;th&gt;Upgrade&lt;&#x2F;th&gt;&lt;&#x2F;tr&gt;&lt;&#x2F;thead&gt;&lt;tbody&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
	&lt;td&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;items&quot;
		data-armory-ids=&quot;95808&quot;
		data-armory-95808-upgrades=&quot;24615&quot;
		data-armory-95808-stat=&quot;1077&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;
	&lt;td&gt;Pistol&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;
	&lt;td&gt;Berserker&#x27;s&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;
	&lt;td&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;items&quot;
		data-armory-ids=&quot;24615&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Force&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;tr&gt;
&lt;tr&gt;
	&lt;td&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;items&quot; s
		data-armory-ids=&quot;95808&quot;
		data-armory-95808-upgrades=&quot;24868&quot;
		data-armory-95808-stat=&quot;1077&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt;&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;
	&lt;td&gt;Pistol&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;
	&lt;td&gt;Berserker&#x27;s&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;
	&lt;td&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;items&quot;
		data-armory-ids=&quot;24868&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Impact&lt;&#x2F;td&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;tr&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;tbody&gt;&lt;&#x2F;table&gt;
&lt;div style=‘clear:both;’&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;&#x2F;div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This will allow you to upkeep damage at range while it is unsafe to stay within melee range of the boss. Examples of such a scenario would include Lesser&#x2F;Greater Dip phase on Dhuum, or 40&#x2F;30&#x2F;20% phase on Qadim The Peerless.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;While in Pistol&#x2F;Pistol, replace your Loop with:&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Loop:&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;13011&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Unload (Pistol 3) × 3&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Dodge&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Repeat&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As fully chanelling &lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;13011&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Unload without cancelling it refunds the &lt;strong&gt;Initiative&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt; used, you can use it endlessly.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Finally, Throw Magnetic Bomb is a possible stolen skill from some raid bosses. It is both a large damage and CC skill, and should be used between steps 2 &amp;amp; 3 of your loop.&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Examples of bosses that this is particularly effective on include&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bosses:&lt;&#x2F;strong&gt;&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Sabetha (Wing 1)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Samarog (Wing 3)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conjured Amalgamate (Wing 6)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Qadim (Wing 6)&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ol&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;blockquote&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;sustainability-for-solo-ow&quot;&gt;Sustainability for Solo&#x2F;OW&lt;&#x2F;h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You may equip the following for extra sustainability:&lt;&#x2F;p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;items&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;101955&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Relic of Zakiros&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;skills&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;13050&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Signet of Malice&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;armory-inline&quot; data-armory-embed=&quot;traits&quot; data-armory-ids=&quot;1702&quot;&gt;&lt;&#x2F;span&gt; Invigorating Precision&lt;&#x2F;li&gt;
&lt;&#x2F;ul&gt;
